Mr Chen's family has said investigators told them that he was subjected to numerous racial slurs and forced to do excessive sit-ups, push-ups, runs and sprints carrying sandbags as punishment for not being as physically fit as the rest of the platoon.

On the day that he killed himself, he forgot his helmet and water when he went to report to the guardhouse. His superiors forced him to crawl over 100 meters of gravel with all of his equipment when he returned, all the while having other soldiers throw rocks at him.

The investigative hearing recommended 
that Offutt, 32, be court-martialed on charges including assault, 
negligent homicide, and reckless endangerment, a statement from U.S. 
military said after the hearing ended Sunday.

The most serious charge Offutt now faces is negligent homicide, which carries a prison sentence of up to three years.

